cs.GT, cs.SI, cs.CE, cs.MA, cs.DS 

This paper deals with game theory and mechanism design, specifically in the context of an extended El Farol game. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.GT (Game Theory and Mechanism Design). The paper also discusses social networks and their effects, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper involves optimization and finding the minimum social cost, which could be categorized under cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science). The paper also uses mathematical analysis to derive exact characterizations, which could fall under cs.MA (Mathematical Analysis). Finally, the paper deals with decision-making and strategies, which could be categorized under cs.DS (Decision Support).
